{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm here to talk about"},{"time":2000,"text":"the wonder and the mystery"},{"time":5000,"text":"of conscious minds."},{"time":8000,"text":"The wonder is about the fact"},{"time":10000,"text":"that we all woke up this morning"},{"time":12000,"text":"and we had with it"},{"time":14000,"text":"the amazing return of our conscious mind."},{"time":17000,"text":"We recovered minds with a complete sense of self"},{"time":20000,"text":"and a complete sense of our own existence,"},{"time":23000,"text":"yet we hardly ever pause to consider this wonder."},{"time":25000,"text":"We should, in fact,"},{"time":27000,"text":"because without having this possibility of conscious minds,"},{"time":31000,"text":"we would have no knowledge whatsoever"},{"time":33000,"text":"about our humanity;"},{"time":35000,"text":"we would have no knowledge whatsoever about the world."},{"time":38000,"text":"We would have no pains, but also no joys."},{"time":40000,"text":"We would have no access to love"},{"time":43000,"text":"or to the ability to create."},{"time":46000,"text":"And of course, Scott Fitzgerald said famously"},{"time":49000,"text":"that \"he who invented consciousness"},{"time":52000,"text":"would have a lot to be blamed for.\""},{"time":55000,"text":"But he also forgot"},{"time":57000,"text":"that without consciousness,"},{"time":59000,"text":"he would have no access to true happiness"},{"time":62000,"text":"and even the possibility of transcendence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64000,"text":"So much for the wonder, now for the mystery."},{"time":67000,"text":"This is a mystery"},{"time":69000,"text":"that has really been extremely hard to elucidate."},{"time":72000,"text":"All the way back into early philosophy"},{"time":75000,"text":"and certainly throughout the history of neuroscience,"},{"time":78000,"text":"this has been one mystery"},{"time":81000,"text":"that has always resisted elucidation,"},{"time":83000,"text":"has got major controversies."},{"time":85000,"text":"And there are actually many people"},{"time":87000,"text":"that think we should not even touch it;"},{"time":89000,"text":"we should just leave it alone, it's not to be solved."},{"time":91000,"text":"I don't believe that,"},{"time":93000,"text":"and I think the situation is changing."},{"time":95000,"text":"It would be ridiculous to claim"},{"time":97000,"text":"that we know how we make consciousness"},{"time":100000,"text":"in our brains,"},{"time":102000,"text":"but we certainly can begin"},{"time":104000,"text":"to approach the question,"},{"time":106000,"text":"and we can begin to see the shape of a solution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109000,"text":"And one more wonder to celebrate"},{"time":112000,"text":"is the fact that we have imaging technologies"},{"time":116000,"text":"that now allow us to go inside the human brain"},{"time":120000,"text":"and be able to do, for example,"},{"time":122000,"text":"what you're seeing right now."},{"time":124000,"text":"These are images that come from Hanna Damasio's lab,"},{"time":127000,"text":"and which show you, in a living brain,"},{"time":130000,"text":"the reconstruction of that brain."},{"time":132000,"text":"And this is a person who is alive."},{"time":134000,"text":"This is not a person"},{"time":136000,"text":"that is being studied at autopsy."},{"time":139000,"text":"And even more --"},{"time":141000,"text":"and this is something that one can be really amazed about --"},{"time":144000,"text":"is what I'm going to show you next,"},{"time":146000,"text":"which is going underneath the surface of the brain"},{"time":149000,"text":"and actually looking in the living brain"},{"time":152000,"text":"at real connections, real pathways."},{"time":155000,"text":"So all of those colored lines"},{"time":158000,"text":"correspond to bunches of axons,"},{"time":161000,"text":"the fibers that join cell bodies"},{"time":163000,"text":"to synapses."},{"time":166000,"text":"And I'm sorry to disappoint you, they don't come in color."},{"time":168000,"text":"But at any rate, they are there."},{"time":171000,"text":"The colors are codes for the direction,"},{"time":173000,"text":"from whether it is back to front"},{"time":175000,"text":"or vice versa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177000,"text":"At any rate, what is consciousness?"},{"time":180000,"text":"What is a conscious mind?"},{"time":182000,"text":"And we could take a very simple view"},{"time":184000,"text":"and say, well, it is that which we lose"},{"time":188000,"text":"when we fall into deep sleep without dreams,"},{"time":193000,"text":"or when we go under anesthesia,"},{"time":195000,"text":"and it is what we regain"},{"time":197000,"text":"when we recover from sleep"},{"time":199000,"text":"or from anesthesia."},{"time":201000,"text":"But what is exactly that stuff that we lose under anesthesia,"},{"time":205000,"text":"or when we are in deep, dreamless sleep?"},{"time":207000,"text":"Well first of all,"},{"time":209000,"text":"it is a mind,"},{"time":211000,"text":"which is a flow of mental images."},{"time":213000,"text":"And of course consider images"},{"time":215000,"text":"that can be sensory patterns,"},{"time":217000,"text":"visual, such as you're having right now"},{"time":219000,"text":"in relation to the stage and me,"},{"time":221000,"text":"or auditory images,"},{"time":223000,"text":"as you are having now in relation to my words."},{"time":225000,"text":"That flow of mental images"},{"time":227000,"text":"is mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"But there is something else"},{"time":231000,"text":"that we are all experiencing in this room."},{"time":233000,"text":"We are not passive exhibitors"},{"time":235000,"text":"of visual or auditory"},{"time":238000,"text":"or tactile images."},{"time":240000,"text":"We have selves."},{"time":242000,"text":"We have a Me"},{"time":244000,"text":"that is automatically present"},{"time":246000,"text":"in our minds right now."},{"time":248000,"text":"We own our minds."},{"time":250000,"text":"And we have a sense that it's everyone of us"},{"time":253000,"text":"that is experiencing this --"},{"time":255000,"text":"not the person who is sitting next to you."},{"time":258000,"text":"So in order to have a conscious mind,"},{"time":261000,"text":"you have a self within the conscious mind."},{"time":265000,"text":"So a conscious mind is a mind with a self in it."},{"time":268000,"text":"The self introduces the subjective perspective in the mind,"},{"time":271000,"text":"and we are only fully conscious"},{"time":273000,"text":"when self comes to mind."},{"time":275000,"text":"So what we need to know to even address this mystery"},{"time":278000,"text":"is, number one, how are minds are put together in the brain,"},{"time":281000,"text":"and, number two, how selves are constructed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285000,"text":"Now the first part, the first problem,"},{"time":288000,"text":"is relatively easy -- it's not easy at all --"},{"time":291000,"text":"but it is something that has been approached gradually in neuroscience."},{"time":295000,"text":"And it's quite clear that, in order to make minds,"},{"time":298000,"text":"we need to construct neural maps."},{"time":301000,"text":"So imagine a grid, like the one I'm showing you right now,"},{"time":304000,"text":"and now imagine, within that grid,"},{"time":306000,"text":"that two-dimensional sheet,"},{"time":308000,"text":"imagine neurons."},{"time":310000,"text":"And picture, if you will,"},{"time":312000,"text":"a billboard, a digital billboard,"},{"time":314000,"text":"where you have elements"},{"time":316000,"text":"that can be either lit or not."},{"time":318000,"text":"And depending on how you create the pattern"},{"time":321000,"text":"of lighting or not lighting,"},{"time":324000,"text":"the digital elements,"},{"time":326000,"text":"or, for that matter, the neurons in the sheet,"},{"time":328000,"text":"you're going to be able to construct a map."},{"time":330000,"text":"This, of course, is a visual map that I'm showing you,"},{"time":333000,"text":"but this applies to any kind of map --"},{"time":335000,"text":"auditory, for example, in relation to sound frequencies,"},{"time":338000,"text":"or to the maps that we construct with our skin"},{"time":341000,"text":"in relation to an object that we palpate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344000,"text":"Now to bring home the point"},{"time":346000,"text":"of how close it is --"},{"time":348000,"text":"the relationship between the grid of neurons"},{"time":351000,"text":"and the topographical arrangement"},{"time":353000,"text":"of the activity of the neurons"},{"time":355000,"text":"and our mental experience --"},{"time":357000,"text":"I'm going to tell you a personal story."},{"time":359000,"text":"So if I cover my left eye --"},{"time":362000,"text":"I'm talking about me personally, not all of you --"},{"time":364000,"text":"if I cover my left eye,"},{"time":366000,"text":"I look at the grid -- pretty much like the one I'm showing you."},{"time":369000,"text":"Everything is nice and fine and perpendicular."},{"time":372000,"text":"But sometime ago, I discovered"},{"time":374000,"text":"that if I cover my left eye,"},{"time":377000,"text":"instead what I get is this."},{"time":379000,"text":"I look at the grid and I see a warping"},{"time":382000,"text":"at the edge of my central-left field."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385000,"text":"Very odd -- I've analyzed this for a while."},{"time":387000,"text":"But sometime ago,"},{"time":390000,"text":"through the help of an opthamologist colleague of mine,"},{"time":393000,"text":"Carmen Puliafito,"},{"time":395000,"text":"who developed a laser scanner of the retina,"},{"time":398000,"text":"I found out the the following."},{"time":400000,"text":"If I scan my retina"},{"time":402000,"text":"through the horizontal plane that you see there in the little corner,"},{"time":405000,"text":"what I get is the following."},{"time":407000,"text":"On the right side, my retina is perfectly symmetrical."},{"time":410000,"text":"You see the going down towards the fovea"},{"time":413000,"text":"where the optic nerve begins."},{"time":415000,"text":"But on my left retina there is a bump,"},{"time":417000,"text":"which is marked there by the red arrow."},{"time":419000,"text":"And it corresponds to a little cyst"},{"time":421000,"text":"that is located below."},{"time":423000,"text":"And that is exactly what causes"},{"time":426000,"text":"the warping of my visual image."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"So just think of this:"},{"time":431000,"text":"you have a grid of neurons,"},{"time":433000,"text":"and now you have a plane mechanical change"},{"time":437000,"text":"in the position of the grid,"},{"time":439000,"text":"and you get a warping of your mental experience."},{"time":441000,"text":"So this is how close"},{"time":443000,"text":"your mental experience"},{"time":445000,"text":"and the activity of the neurons in the retina,"},{"time":448000,"text":"which is a part of the brain located in the eyeball,"},{"time":451000,"text":"or, for that matter, a sheet of visual cortex."},{"time":454000,"text":"So from the retina"},{"time":456000,"text":"you go onto visual cortex."},{"time":458000,"text":"And of course, the brain adds on"},{"time":460000,"text":"a lot of information"},{"time":462000,"text":"to what is going on"},{"time":464000,"text":"in the signals that come from the retina."},{"time":466000,"text":"And in that image there,"},{"time":468000,"text":"you see a variety of islands"},{"time":470000,"text":"of what I call image-making regions in the brain."},{"time":473000,"text":"You have the green for example,"},{"time":475000,"text":"that corresponds to tactile information,"},{"time":477000,"text":"or the blue that corresponds to auditory information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480000,"text":"And something else that happens"},{"time":482000,"text":"is that those image-making regions"},{"time":485000,"text":"where you have the plotting"},{"time":487000,"text":"of all these neural maps,"},{"time":489000,"text":"can then provide signals"},{"time":491000,"text":"to this ocean of purple that you see around,"},{"time":494000,"text":"which is the association cortex,"},{"time":496000,"text":"where you can make records of what went on"},{"time":499000,"text":"in those islands of image-making."},{"time":501000,"text":"And the great beauty"},{"time":503000,"text":"is that you can then go from memory,"},{"time":506000,"text":"out of those association cortices,"},{"time":508000,"text":"and produce back images"},{"time":511000,"text":"in the very same regions that have perception."},{"time":514000,"text":"So think about how wonderfully convenient and lazy"},{"time":517000,"text":"the brain is."},{"time":519000,"text":"So it provides certain areas"},{"time":521000,"text":"for perception and image-making."},{"time":523000,"text":"And those are exactly the same"},{"time":525000,"text":"that are going to be used for image-making"},{"time":528000,"text":"when we recall information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531000,"text":"So far the mystery of the conscious mind"},{"time":534000,"text":"is diminishing a little bit"},{"time":536000,"text":"because we have a general sense"},{"time":538000,"text":"of how we make these images."},{"time":540000,"text":"But what about the self?"},{"time":542000,"text":"The self is really the elusive problem."},{"time":545000,"text":"And for a long time,"},{"time":547000,"text":"people did not even want to touch it,"},{"time":549000,"text":"because they'd say,"},{"time":551000,"text":"\"How can you have this reference point, this stability,"},{"time":554000,"text":"that is required to maintain"},{"time":556000,"text":"the continuity of selves day after day?\""},{"time":559000,"text":"And I thought about a solution to this problem."},{"time":562000,"text":"It's the following."},{"time":564000,"text":"We generate brain maps"},{"time":566000,"text":"of the body's interior"},{"time":568000,"text":"and use them as the reference for all other maps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571000,"text":"So let me tell you just a little bit about how I came to this."},{"time":574000,"text":"I came to this because,"},{"time":576000,"text":"if you're going to have a reference that we know as self --"},{"time":580000,"text":"the Me, the I"},{"time":582000,"text":"in our own processing --"},{"time":585000,"text":"we need to have something that is stable,"},{"time":587000,"text":"something that does not deviate much"},{"time":590000,"text":"from day to day."},{"time":592000,"text":"Well it so happens that we have a singular body."},{"time":594000,"text":"We have one body, not two, not three."},{"time":597000,"text":"And so that is a beginning."},{"time":599000,"text":"There is just one reference point, which is the body."},{"time":601000,"text":"But then, of course, the body has many parts,"},{"time":604000,"text":"and things grow at different rates,"},{"time":606000,"text":"and they have different sizes and different people;"},{"time":608000,"text":"however, not so with the interior."},{"time":611000,"text":"The things that have to do"},{"time":613000,"text":"with what is known as our internal milieu --"},{"time":615000,"text":"for example, the whole management"},{"time":617000,"text":"of the chemistries within our body"},{"time":619000,"text":"are, in fact, extremely maintained"},{"time":621000,"text":"day after day"},{"time":623000,"text":"for one very good reason."},{"time":625000,"text":"If you deviate too much"},{"time":627000,"text":"in the parameters"},{"time":629000,"text":"that are close to the midline"},{"time":631000,"text":"of that life-permitting survival range,"},{"time":634000,"text":"you go into disease or death."},{"time":636000,"text":"So we have an in-built system"},{"time":639000,"text":"within our own lives"},{"time":641000,"text":"that ensures some kind of continuity."},{"time":644000,"text":"I like to call it an almost infinite sameness from day to day."},{"time":647000,"text":"Because if you don't have that sameness, physiologically,"},{"time":651000,"text":"you're going to be sick or you're going to die."},{"time":653000,"text":"So that's one more element for this continuity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":656000,"text":"And the final thing"},{"time":658000,"text":"is that there is a very tight coupling"},{"time":660000,"text":"between the regulation of our body within the brain"},{"time":664000,"text":"and the body itself,"},{"time":666000,"text":"unlike any other coupling."},{"time":669000,"text":"So for example, I'm making images of you,"},{"time":671000,"text":"but there's no physiological bond"},{"time":674000,"text":"between the images I have of you as an audience"},{"time":677000,"text":"and my brain."},{"time":679000,"text":"However, there is a close, permanently maintained bond"},{"time":683000,"text":"between the body regulating parts of my brain"},{"time":686000,"text":"and my own body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688000,"text":"So here's how it looks. Look at the region there."},{"time":691000,"text":"There is the brain stem in between the cerebral cortex"},{"time":694000,"text":"and the spinal cord."},{"time":696000,"text":"And it is within that region"},{"time":698000,"text":"that I'm going to highlight now"},{"time":700000,"text":"that we have this housing"},{"time":703000,"text":"of all the life-regulation devices"},{"time":706000,"text":"of the body."},{"time":708000,"text":"This is so specific that, for example,"},{"time":711000,"text":"if you look at the part that is covered in red"},{"time":714000,"text":"in the upper part of the brain stem,"},{"time":716000,"text":"if you damage that as a result of a stroke, for example,"},{"time":719000,"text":"what you get is coma"},{"time":721000,"text":"or vegetative state,"},{"time":723000,"text":"which is a state, of course,"},{"time":725000,"text":"in which your mind disappears,"},{"time":727000,"text":"your consciousness disappears."},{"time":730000,"text":"What happens then actually"},{"time":732000,"text":"is that you lose the grounding of the self,"},{"time":735000,"text":"you have no longer access to any feeling of your own existence,"},{"time":738000,"text":"and, in fact, there can be images going on,"},{"time":741000,"text":"being formed in the cerebral cortex,"},{"time":743000,"text":"except you don't know they're there."},{"time":745000,"text":"You have, in effect, lost consciousness"},{"time":748000,"text":"when you have damage to that red section of the brain stem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752000,"text":"But if you consider the green part of the brain stem,"},{"time":755000,"text":"nothing like that happens."},{"time":757000,"text":"It is that specific."},{"time":759000,"text":"So in that green component of the brain stem,"},{"time":762000,"text":"if you damage it, and often it happens,"},{"time":765000,"text":"what you get is complete paralysis,"},{"time":767000,"text":"but your conscious mind is maintained."},{"time":770000,"text":"You feel, you know, you have a fully conscious mind"},{"time":773000,"text":"that you can report very indirectly."},{"time":776000,"text":"This is a horrific condition. You don't want to see it."},{"time":779000,"text":"And people are, in fact, imprisoned"},{"time":781000,"text":"within their own bodies,"},{"time":783000,"text":"but they do have a mind."},{"time":785000,"text":"There was a very interesting film,"},{"time":787000,"text":"one of the rare good films done"},{"time":789000,"text":"about a situation like this,"},{"time":791000,"text":"by Julian Schnabel some years ago"},{"time":793000,"text":"about a patient that was in that condition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796000,"text":"So now I'm going to show you a picture."},{"time":798000,"text":"I promise not to say anything about this,"},{"time":800000,"text":"except this is to frighten you."},{"time":802000,"text":"It's just to tell you"},{"time":804000,"text":"that in that red section of the brain stem,"},{"time":807000,"text":"there are, to make it simple,"},{"time":809000,"text":"all those little squares that correspond to modules"},{"time":812000,"text":"that actually make brain maps"},{"time":815000,"text":"of different aspects of our interior,"},{"time":818000,"text":"different aspects of our body."},{"time":820000,"text":"They are exquisitely topographic"},{"time":823000,"text":"and they are exquisitely interconnected"},{"time":825000,"text":"in a recursive pattern."},{"time":827000,"text":"And it is out of this and out of this tight coupling"},{"time":830000,"text":"between the brain stem and the body"},{"time":832000,"text":"that I believe -- and I could be wrong,"},{"time":834000,"text":"but I don't think I am --"},{"time":836000,"text":"that you generate this mapping of the body"},{"time":839000,"text":"that provides the grounding for the self"},{"time":842000,"text":"and that comes in the form of feelings --"},{"time":844000,"text":"primordial feelings, by the way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":846000,"text":"So what is the picture that we get here?"},{"time":848000,"text":"Look at \"cerebral cortex,\" look at \"brain stem,\""},{"time":850000,"text":"look at \"body,\""},{"time":852000,"text":"and you get the picture of the interconnectivity"},{"time":855000,"text":"in which you have the brain stem providing the grounding for the self"},{"time":859000,"text":"in a very tight interconnection with the body."},{"time":862000,"text":"And you have the cerebral cortex"},{"time":864000,"text":"providing the great spectacle of our minds"},{"time":867000,"text":"with the profusion of images"},{"time":869000,"text":"that are, in fact, the contents of our minds"},{"time":872000,"text":"and that we normally pay most attention to,"},{"time":875000,"text":"as we should, because that's really"},{"time":877000,"text":"the film that is rolling in our minds."},{"time":879000,"text":"But look at the arrows."},{"time":881000,"text":"They're not there for looks."},{"time":883000,"text":"They're there because there's this very close interaction."},{"time":886000,"text":"You cannot have a conscious mind"},{"time":888000,"text":"if you don't have the interaction"},{"time":890000,"text":"between cerebral cortex and brain stem."},{"time":892000,"text":"You cannot have a conscious mind"},{"time":894000,"text":"if you don't have the interaction"},{"time":896000,"text":"between the brain stem and the body."}]},{"cues":[{"time":898000,"text":"Another thing that is interesting"},{"time":900000,"text":"is that the brain stem that we have"},{"time":902000,"text":"is shared with a variety of other species."},{"time":904000,"text":"So throughout vertebrates,"},{"time":906000,"text":"the design of the brain stem is very similar to ours,"},{"time":909000,"text":"which is one of the reasons why I think"},{"time":911000,"text":"those other species have conscious minds like we do."},{"time":914000,"text":"Except that they're not as rich as ours,"},{"time":917000,"text":"because they don't have a cerebral cortex like we do."},{"time":919000,"text":"That's where the difference is."},{"time":921000,"text":"And I strongly disagree with the idea"},{"time":924000,"text":"that consciousness should be considered"},{"time":927000,"text":"as the great product of the cerebral cortex."},{"time":929000,"text":"Only the wealth of our minds is,"},{"time":931000,"text":"not the very fact that we have a self"},{"time":934000,"text":"that we can refer"},{"time":936000,"text":"to our own existence,"},{"time":938000,"text":"and that we have any sense of person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942000,"text":"Now there are three levels of self to consider --"},{"time":945000,"text":"the proto, the core and the autobiographical."},{"time":948000,"text":"The first two are shared"},{"time":950000,"text":"with many, many other species,"},{"time":952000,"text":"and they are really coming out"},{"time":954000,"text":"largely of the brain stem"},{"time":956000,"text":"and whatever there is of cortex in those species."},{"time":959000,"text":"It's the autobiographical self"},{"time":961000,"text":"which some species have, I think."},{"time":963000,"text":"Cetaceans and primates have also"},{"time":966000,"text":"an autobiographical self to a certain degree."},{"time":968000,"text":"And everybody's dogs at home"},{"time":970000,"text":"have an autobiographical self to a certain degree."},{"time":973000,"text":"But the novelty is here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975000,"text":"The autobiographical self is built"},{"time":977000,"text":"on the basis of past memories"},{"time":979000,"text":"and memories of the plans that we have made;"},{"time":982000,"text":"it's the lived past and the anticipated future."},{"time":985000,"text":"And the autobiographical self"},{"time":987000,"text":"has prompted extended memory, reasoning,"},{"time":990000,"text":"imagination, creativity and language."},{"time":992000,"text":"And out of that came the instruments of culture --"},{"time":995000,"text":"religions, justice,"},{"time":997000,"text":"trade, the arts, science, technology."},{"time":999000,"text":"And it is within that culture"},{"time":1001000,"text":"that we really can get --"},{"time":1003000,"text":"and this is the novelty --"},{"time":1005000,"text":"something that is not entirely set by our biology."},{"time":1009000,"text":"It is developed in the cultures."},{"time":1011000,"text":"It developed in collectives of human beings."},{"time":1015000,"text":"And this is, of course, the culture"},{"time":1017000,"text":"where we have developed something that I like to call"},{"time":1020000,"text":"socio-cultural regulation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022000,"text":"And finally, you could rightly ask,"},{"time":1024000,"text":"why care about this?"},{"time":1026000,"text":"Why care if it is the brain stem or the cerebral cortex"},{"time":1029000,"text":"and how this is made?"},{"time":1031000,"text":"Three reasons. First, curiosity."},{"time":1033000,"text":"Primates are extremely curious --"},{"time":1035000,"text":"and humans most of all."},{"time":1037000,"text":"And if we are interested, for example,"},{"time":1040000,"text":"in the fact that anti-gravity"},{"time":1042000,"text":"is pulling galaxies away from the Earth,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"why should we not be interested in what is going on"},{"time":1046000,"text":"inside of human beings?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1049000,"text":"Second, understanding society and culture."},{"time":1051000,"text":"We should look"},{"time":1053000,"text":"at how society and culture"},{"time":1055000,"text":"in this socio-cultural regulation"},{"time":1057000,"text":"are a work in progress."},{"time":1059000,"text":"And finally, medicine."},{"time":1061000,"text":"Let's not forget that some of the worst diseases"},{"time":1063000,"text":"of humankind"},{"time":1065000,"text":"are diseases such as depression,"},{"time":1067000,"text":"Alzheimer's disease, drug addiction."},{"time":1070000,"text":"Think of strokes that can devastate your mind"},{"time":1073000,"text":"or render you unconscious."},{"time":1075000,"text":"You have no prayer"},{"time":1078000,"text":"of treating those diseases effectively"},{"time":1081000,"text":"and in a non-serendipitous way"},{"time":1083000,"text":"if you do not know how this works."},{"time":1085000,"text":"So that's a very good reason"},{"time":1087000,"text":"beyond curiosity"},{"time":1089000,"text":"to justify what we're doing,"},{"time":1091000,"text":"and to justify having some interest in what is going on in our brains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1094000,"text":"Thank you for your attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1096000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}